"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-health-archive-2024-08-wyatt-sanford-takes-punch-during-olympic-boxing-match-679327\", \"text\": \"Canada's Wyatt Sanford takes a punch on his way to a win.  In the split-second after taking a huge punch to the face, Canada's Wyatt Sanford was photographed during a match against Uzbekistan's Ruslan Abdullaev in the men's 63.5-kilogram quarterfinal boxing event at the North Paris Arena, in Villepinte. These sorts of photos are fairly common in boxing coverage, but that does not take away from their impact-as they reveal shockwaves rippling through a person's surprisingly flexible face and hint at the pain and disorientation the boxer surely feels. Sanford went on to win the match, setting himself up for a medal.  Previously:  July 31:Sweden's Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m, Up Close and Underwater  July 30:Celebrating a Winning Women's Gymnastics Team Effort  July 29:Surfer Filipe Toledo Gets the Barrel  July 28:An Equestrian Leaps Through the Antlers  July 27:A Fencer's Moment of Victory  TheAtlantic.com \\u00a92026The Atlantic Monthly Group. All Rights Reserved.  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply\"}"